{
  "texts": [
    "\"MCC\", \"ACC\" and \"CORR\" denote Matthews correlation coefficient, accuracy, and Pearson correlation coefficient respectively.",
    "This benchmark includes 42.1K training instances, 4.67K validation instances, and 4.69K testing instances.",
    "Following previous studies, we used the official evaluation script to compute BLEU (Papineni et al., 2002), NIST (Belz and Reiter, 2006), METEOR (Banerjee and Lavie, 2005), ROUGE-L (Lin, 2004) and CIDEr (Vedantam et al., 2014) scores.",
    "For evaluations using GPT-2, we ran experiment for 3 times using distinct random seeds and reported the average results.",
    "The random seeds used for these experiments were 42, 43, and 44."
  ]
}